article.headline: DePaul 75, Albany, N.Y. 64
article.story: CHICAGO -- Dar Tucker scored 23 points and Will Walker added 19 to lead DePaul to a 75-64 victory over the University at Albany on Monday night. Jabari Currie scored 11 points and Jeremiah Kelly added 10 points for DePaul (1-0), which jumped out to a 11-2 lead early and 43-28 at halftime. A 3-pointer by Louis Barraza pulled Albany (0-2) to within 57-51 with 8:16 left in the game, but the Blue Demons held the Great Danes off, despite shooting 31 percent in the second half. Mike Johnson led Albany with 16 points. Barraza added 13 points, including three 3-pointers, and Will Harris had 11. DePaul played a rare home game on the Lincoln Park campus in front of 3,502 fans. The rest of their home games will be played at the Allstate Arena in the northwest suburbs.
